  "A pharmaceutical company tests drug dosage (mg) versus effectiveness (%): (10, 30), (20, 55), (30, 70), (40, 75), (50, 70), (60, 55). The quadratic regression gives y = -0.05x^2 + 4x - 5 with r^2 = 0.99. What dosage maximizes effectiveness?": "",
  "x = -4/(2(-0.05)) = -4/(-0.1) = 40 mg. Maximum effectiveness: -0.05(1600) + 4(40) - 5 = -80 + 160 - 5 = 75%. The optimal dosage is 40 mg with 75% effectiveness.": ""
